%md
# Analyze Apache projects using github stats

paragraphs.title: Get the list of Apache projects from github
paragraphs.text:
%pyspark

import requests

repo_list_json = []

headers = {'Authorization': 'token ***REMOVED***'}
base_url = "https://api.github.com/orgs/apache/repos"
print("Getting " + base_url)
r = requests.get(base_url, headers = headers)
repo_list_json.extend(r.json())
next_link = r.links.get("next")
while next_link is not None:
    next_link_url = next_link.get('url')
    print("Getting " + next_link_url)
    r = requests.get(next_link_url, headers = headers)
    repo_list_json.extend(r.json())
    next_link = r.links.get("next")

paragraphs.title: Extract interesting data into a data frame
paragraphs.text:
%pyspark

from pyspark.sql.types import *

projects = []

for proj_num in range(0, len(repo_list_json)):
    project = repo_list_json[proj_num]
    project_description = {'name': project.get('name'), 'start_date': project.get('created_at'), 'forks': project.get('forks_count'), 'watchers': project.get('watchers_count'), 'size': project.get('size'), 'language': project.get('language')}
    projects.append(project_description)

schema = StructType([StructField('name', StringType(), True), 
                     StructField('start_date', DateType(), True), 
                     StructField('forks', FloatType(), True), 
                     StructField('watchers', FloatType(), True, True), 
                     StructField('size', FloatType(), True), 
                     StructField('language', StringType(), True)
                     ])

project_df = sqlContext.createDataFrame(projects)
project_df.printSchema()
project_df.registerTempTable('projects')

paragraphs.title: Save the dataframe so we don't have to re-create it from github
Which Apache projects are watched the most?
paragraphs.text:
%sql
select name, watchers, forks, start_date, language, size 
from projects
order by watchers desc

paragraphs.title: Take a look at the watcher to fork ratio
paragraphs.text:
%sql
select name, watchers, forks, watchers / forks as watcher_fork_ratio, start_date, language, size 
from projects
order by watcher_fork_ratio desc

paragraphs.title: Search stackoverflow for popularity
paragraphs.text:
%pyspark

import requests

so_tags_search_url = 'http://api.stackexchange.com/2.2/tags?order=desc&sort=popular&site=stackoverflow&inname='
tag_list_json = []

for project in projects:
    project_name = project.get("name")
#    if project_name.
    print("Getting tags for " + project_name)
    r = requests.get(so_tags_search_url + project_name)
    tag_list_json.extend(r.json())
